description:
I was there two weekends ago for brunch with a couple of friends and could not stop staring at this woman.  After a while it clicked and I realized it was Pam from Real World SF, season 3!!  I then studied her company and say that Judd was sitting across from her with what could only be their 5 ish year old boy.  SUPER cute.  On the way out Judd walked along behind us and I couldn't help but want to scream, "I loved watching you on TV when I was like,  12 years old!"

But anyway;

It has a relatively quick wait to get a table (get one outside!).  The food is yummy, the omelets are enormous, the mimosas are really good, the service is decent, the bathroom is a little scary, the dogs can sit in the outside section, the jams are yummy, the potatoes are cooked well, the noise level is tolerable, the decor is average, the price is great.
